fields.title: Last Orders
fields.description:
Last Orders is a student written show that was first put on at University of Warwick via Freshblood New Writing Society. Since the success of the first sold out run, we have made a few tweaks and refinements to take this magnificent show to Edinburgh Fringe! A brilliant opportunity for all involved with some first time Fringe goers.

Our show follows Kenneth's first day working at the McGonagall Tavern, though as we are introduced to witches, a couple rats, the uptight manager, the creative yet unstable chef and the critic. Well, we are in for a ride.

fields.title: Chicken Soup with Barley
fields.description: Chicken Soup with Barley is a 1956 play by Arnold Wesker that grapples with the breakdown of an ideology and a family in parallel, synthesising the personal, political, and philosophical into an odyssey across decades that reveals the power of brotherhood even in a country that always seems in decline. Our production would modernise the text and give it a queer edge to explore the prescience of community and caring in the modern age.

fields.title: The Strongest Block Floor
fields.description: An artistic masterpiece depicting our well loved flatmate Daiki, of whom has been residing with us for almost a year. He will only be with us for a few more weeks, but his effect on Warwick University life will be felt for generations to come. No man who has been graced by his presence will be left without a smile, and this artform exists to immortalise and encapsulate only a fraction of his glory.

fields.title: Art By Balqis: The Beauty of Malaysian Culture
fields.description: I’m a self-taught acrylic, acrylic paint pouring, watercolour and oil painter. Recently, I just released a watercolour Eid card collection during Eid. The designs range from Malaysian Batik motives and traditional Malay delicacies. For this festival, I wish to create 3-4 new artworks relating to the theme of the diversity of the Malaysian culture. I wish to display my artwork during Warwick’ Art Festival.

fields.title: Falasteen (tapestry)
fields.description: I crochet tapestry wall-hangings which have arabic calligraphy and/or other designs which are used as decoration or art pieces. This piece is called Falasteen, and is has aspects of the Palestinian identity, a white dove, and olive branches, as well as some calligraphy. What my pieces do is show Islam, or Islamic concepts as something artistic. This piece is both a piece of activism, and something artistic.

fields.title: Sreekeerthana Kamalesh
fields.description:
Indian Gujarati Dance Form Called Garba

Garba is a popular form of folk dance that originated in the state of Gujarat in India. Traditionally, it is performed during the nine-day Hindu festival of Navaratri. It is a joyful style of dance, based on a circular pattern and characterized by a sweeping action from side to side.

fields.title: Art and Reality: Warwick Student Documentary Production
fields.description: Five documentaries made by Warwick student in total. They cover different themes, including the use of AI in art, marine life, student activism and a football team at Warwick. They are all the entries to the Warwick Documentary Society, but we would like to ensure that credits are given to all student filmmakers. We hope that the screening can encourage students to create their own documentaries and appreciate creative talents around them.

We would like to set up a room of stalls displaying the work of our society members, with a central table for art + crafts:
- The work shown will be a mix of art forms, including some showcases of 2D/3D models, cosplay projects and traditional/digital art pieces.

fields.title: Behind the Curtain / Wired Tensions
fields.description: Step into the world of your wildest dreams as kishan and danny bring to life an original piece of fan "fiction" through the power of spoken word. In this captivating (erotic?) performance, we will take you on an emotional journey where beloved classic characters come to life in new and unexpected ways. Through the rhythm of our words and the depth of our storytelling, you'll experience the excitement, the tension, and the romance of our enemies to lovers prophecy.
